    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Class for storing data required for delayed unary operations, such as the operand (e.g. the matrix to which the operation is to be applied) and the unary operator (e.g. inverse). The operand is stored as a reference (which can be optimised away), while the operator is &quot;stored&quot; through the template definition (op_type). The operands can be &apos;<ref refid="classMat" kindref="compound">Mat</ref>&apos;, &apos;<ref refid="classRow" kindref="compound">Row</ref>&apos;, &apos;<ref refid="classCol" kindref="compound">Col</ref>&apos;, &apos;<ref refid="classOp" kindref="compound">Op</ref>&apos;, and &apos;<ref refid="classGlue" kindref="compound">Glue</ref>&apos;. Note that as &apos;<ref refid="classGlue" kindref="compound">Glue</ref>&apos; can be one of the operands, more than one matrix can be stored.</para><para>For example, we could have: <ref refid="classOp" kindref="compound">Op</ref>&lt; Glue&lt; Mat, Mat, glue_times &gt;, <ref refid="classop__htrans" kindref="compound">op_htrans</ref> &gt; </para>    </detaileddescription>
